definitions.definition: The wood from any gymnosperm , without regard to how soft this wood is.
Wood of this kind, but limited to those that are commercial timbers .
The tree or tree species that yields this wood.
examples: SYP is a softwood , but it is harder than many hardwoods.
This softwood has been planted extensively throughout Scotland.
You should have used softwood for the frame of this shed, instead of overbuilding it like this.

main_definition: ( uncountable , chiefly botany ) The wood from any gymnosperm , without regard to how soft this wood is.
secondary_definitions: ( countable , in more general use ) Wood of this kind, but limited to those that are commercial timbers .
( countable , forestry ) The tree or tree species that yields this wood.
